# Root build context ignore — the backend image builds from the REPO ROOT (it needs both backend/
# and db/baseline/schema.sql in their real relative layout; see backend/Dockerfile). Keep the
# context lean: exclude everything heavy/irrelevant. The Dockerfile COPYs only what it needs
# (backend/, db/, deploy/gcp/seed.py, and one reference sample), so a broad allow-list here is safe.

# Python / build noise
**/.venv
**/venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.coverage
**/*.egg-info

# Node / frontend (the frontend has its OWN image + context; never needed in the backend image)
frontend/node_modules
frontend/.next
frontend/out

# Secrets / env
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store

# Large data dirs not needed by the backend image. reference/ is 150MB+; the backend Dockerfile
# copies ONLY the single potato legacy sample it needs (see the explicit COPY there), so ignore the
# rest of reference/ and the vault/screenshots/etc. (NB: a later COPY can still reach an ignored
# path only if re-included; we instead keep the one needed file out of these globs.)
reference/samples/_allocation_models
reference/samples/*.docx
reference/samples/*.html
reference/samples/itrade_*
reference/samples/bid_*
var
screenshots
audit
mcp
specs
docs
project
docker-compose*.yml
